as the final legendary skywalker's family conflict this movie did a good job maybe not for the critics who's expect more from this final conclusion but I think with all the tribute from the previous episodes the rise of skywalker once again did it right
The Rise of Skywalker is a muddled bunch of nostalgia at makes little sense in the scope of the first six Star Wars Movies.  the movie fails its own characters and story.
What a fitting end to this epic saga. It's an emotional rollercoaster. After 9 episodes and 40 years, the finale is worth the wait.
The best one of the new trilogy

Redeemed (without excusing) Episode VIII.
I loved the traditional formula, and all the clever mirroring that they did. And especially the few nods to fandom and even a subtle acknowledgement that Episode VIII stuffed up in their Luke character arc.

*SPOILER FREE REVIEW*

it was awesome! Was very different compared to TFA and TLJ. I wouldn't say it made risks unlike TLJ it played it a bit more safe. A few things JJ changed due to rian' s work but works pretty well for the story. C3-PO had more involvement unlike the last 2 and the film gets brought to a very satisfying end to the saga. I enjoy TLJ but this was better! Definitely gonna see again!

This is Star Wars.

If you're looking for the nostalgia trip to close the final chapter of the Star Wars saga, this is it. Two hours and twenty one minutes of cinematic excellence that brings long deserved closure to dozens of character arcs, with a masterful weave of emotionally stirring moments along the way.

I had my problems with VIII, but knowing that it led to this I can honestly say I've forgotten them.

Go watch!
